her changes) and let me know of any issue you [...]\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:32:\"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/\";a:1:{s:7:\"creator\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:5:\"frank\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:40:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/\";a:1:{s:7:\"encoded\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:2039:\"<p>Autoptimize 2.5 is almost ready! It features a new &#8220;Images&#8221;-tab to house all Image optimization options, including support for lazy-loading images and WebP (<a href=\"https://calendar.perfplanet.com/2018/dont-use-jpeg-xr-on-the-web/\">the only next-gen image format that really matters</a>, no?);<br />\n<a href=\"http://blog.futtta.be/wp-content/uploads/2019/03/ao_images.png\"><img class=\"alignright size-large wp-image-10821\" src=\"http://blog.futtta.be/wp-content/uploads/2019/03/ao_images-1024x506.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"625\" height=\"309\" srcset=\"http://blog.futtta.be/wp-content/uploads/2019/03/ao_images-1024x506.png 1024w, http://blog.futtta.be/wp-content/uploads/2019/03/ao_images-300x148.png 300w, http://blog.futtta.be/wp-content/uploads/2019/03/ao_images-624x308.png 624w, http://blog.futtta.be/wp-content/uploads/2019/03/ao_images.png 1584w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 625px) 100vw, 625px\" /></a></p>\n<p>So <a href=\"https://github.com/futtta/autoptimize/archive/beta.zip\">download the beta</a> and test lazy-loading and WebP (and <a href=\"https://github.com/futtta/autoptimize/commits/beta\">all of the other changes</a>) and let me know of any issue you might find!</p>\n<div class=\'yarpp-related-rss\'>\n<p>Possibly related twitterless twaddle:<ul>\n<li><a href=\"https://blog.futtta.be/2018/12/31/autoptimize-2-5-beta-image-lazy-loading/\" rel=\"bookmark\" title=\"Autoptimize 2.5 beta: image lazy loading\">Autoptimize 2.5 beta: image lazy loading </a></li>\n<li><a href=\"https://