 6</p>\n						<p>Hi<br />\nI have a query about something similar to what is reported in this topic<br />\n<a href=\"https://wordpress.org/support/topic/w3tc-non-existent-js-and-css-in-cache-minify-throw-errors/page/2/\" rel=\"nofollow\">https://wordpress.org/support/topic/w3tc-non-existent-js-and-css-in-cache-minify-throw-errors/page/2/</a></p>\n<p>My site is cached on cloudflare.<br />\nWhen testing my site on gtmetrix (and only when using the chrome option) I get the &#8220;Serve resources from a consistent URL&#8221; flag and two copies of the minified js are found<br />\n    <a href=\"http://rathfarnhamparish.ie/wp-content/cache/minify/d8750.default.include.248d2c.js\" rel=\"nofollow\">http://rathfarnhamparish.ie/wp-content/cache/minify/d8750.default.include.248d2c.js</a><br />\n    <a href=\"http://rathfarnhamparish.ie/wp-content/cache/minify/d8750.default.include.cb5f39.js\" rel=\"nofollow\">http://rathfarnhamparish.ie/wp-content/cache/minify/d8750.default.include.cb5f39.js</a></p>\n<p>What is interesting is I know exactly how to reproduce this. It only happens on pages on my site where the url is redirected to another page.<br />\n<a href=\"http://rathfarnhamparish.ie/baptism/\" rel=\"nofollow\">http://rathfarnhamparish.ie/baptism/</a> is redirected to<br />\n<a href=\"http://rathfarnhamparish.ie/sacraments/baptism/\" rel=\"nofollow\">http://rathfarnhamparish.ie/sacraments/baptism/</a><br />\nand I only get &#8220;Serve resources from a consistent URL&#8221; on the first not the second.</p>\n<p>The above phenomenon only happens on gmetrix using chrome. There is no doubling up when using Firefox.<br />\nIt seems clear that the combination of w3tc and cloudflare is picking up a copy of the minified file from both the original url and the redirected page.</p>\n<p>I could avoid all of this by not using redirected pages but unfortunately there doesn&#8217;t seem to be a way to avoid (what amount to) redirects for a static front page in WordPress. </p>\n<p>Any help appreciated. I hope the problem being identifiable and reproducible helps.</p><img src=\"http://feeds.feedburner.com/~r/W3TOTALCACHE/~4/dC5lVVGw7QE\" height=\"1\" width=\"1\" alt=\"\"/>\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:32:\"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/\";a:1:{s:7:\"creator\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:6:\"joblog\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:42:\"http://rssnamespace.org/feedburner/ext/1.0\";a:1:{s:8:\"origLink\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:95:\"https://wordpress.org/support/topic/w3tc-and-cloudflare-doubling-up-minified-files-on-redirect/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}}}}}s:27:\"http://www.w3.org/2005/Atom\";a:1:{s:4:\"link\";a:3:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:0:\"\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:1:{s:0:\"\";a:3:{s:3:\"rel\";s:4:\"self\";s:4:\"type\";s:19:\"application/rss+xml\";s:4:\"href\";s:40:\"http://feeds.feedburner.com/W3TOTALCACHE\";}}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:1;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:0:\"\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:1:{s:0:\"\";a:3:{s:3:\"rel\";s:4:\"self\";s:4:\"type\";s:19:\"application/rss+xml\";s:4:\"href\";s:40:\"http://feeds.feedburner.com/W3TOTALCACHE\";}}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:2;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:0:\"\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:1:{s:0:\"\";a:2:{s:3:\"rel\";s:3:\"hub\";s:4:\"href\";s:32:\"http://pubsubhubbub.appspot.com/\";}}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:42:\"http://rssnamespace.org/feedburner/ext/1.0\";a:1:{s:4:\"info\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:0:\"\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:1:{s:0:\"\";a:1:{s:3:\"uri\";s:12:\"w3totalcache\";}}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:28:\"http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml\";a:1:{s:4:\"me